---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Terms & Disclaimers | NorthWestern Diesel"
  description="Terms of service and disclaimers for NorthWestern Diesel mobile diesel repair services."
>
  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="hero-container">
      <h1 class="page-title">Terms & Disclaimers</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Service Terms, Limitations, and Liability Information</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Terms Content -->
  <section class="legal-content-section">
    <div class="legal-content-container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        <p class="legal-intro">
          By using the services of NorthWestern Diesel ("we," "our," or "us"), you agree to the following 
          terms and conditions. Please read these terms carefully before requesting service.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Service Terms</h2>
        <h3>1.1 Service Availability</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Services are provided on a mobile basis within our designated service areas (DFW: 100-mile radius, Spokane: 75-mile radius)</li>
          <li>Service availability is subject to technician availability and scheduling</li>
          <li>Spokane location services are currently limited - please call before requesting service to confirm availability</li>
          <li>We reserve the right to refuse service at our discretion</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.2 Pricing and Payment</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>All pricing is based on hourly rates as displayed on our website</li>
          <li>Minimum service charges apply as specified (2-4 hours depending on time/day)</li>
          <li>Prices do not include parts, taxes, or additional fees unless specifically stated</li>
          <li>Travel/drive time may apply for locations outside standard service radius</li>
          <li>Payment is due upon completion of service unless other arrangements are made in advance</li>
          <li>We accept cash, check, and major credit cards</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.3 Service Hours</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Regular Service:</strong> Monday-Friday, 6AM-6PM</li>
          <li><strong>After-Hours Service:</strong> Available at premium rates (6PM-6AM weekdays)</li>
          <li><strong>Weekend Service:</strong> Available at premium rates</li>
          <li><strong>Emergency Service:</strong> Available 24/7 at premium rates</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Service Limitations</h2>
        <h3>2.1 Diagnostic Limitations</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>While we use advanced diagnostic equipment, some issues may require additional testing or shop-based diagnostics</li>
          <li>Complex issues may require multiple visits or referral to specialized facilities</li>
          <li>We cannot guarantee that all issues will be resolved in a single service call</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Parts and Equipment</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Parts availability may vary - some parts may need to be ordered and installed at a later date</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for delays caused by parts availability or manufacturer backorders</li>
          <li>Customer-provided parts may be used at customer's risk and may void warranties</li>
          <li>We reserve the right to refuse installation of customer-provided parts if they are incompatible or unsafe</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.3 Equipment Condition</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Services are provided on equipment "as-is" at the time of service</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for pre-existing conditions or damage not caused by our service</li>
          <li>Some equipment may be unsafe to operate or repair - we reserve the right to refuse service on unsafe equipment</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Warranty and Guarantees</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We provide a warranty on labor performed, subject to the following conditions:
            <ul>
              <li>Warranty period: 90 days or 5,000 miles, whichever comes first</li>
              <li>Warranty covers defects in workmanship only</li>
              <li>Warranty does not cover parts (parts are covered by manufacturer warranty)</li>
              <li>Warranty is void if equipment is modified, misused, or serviced by others after our service</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>We do not guarantee that repairs will prevent future failures or issues</li>
          <li>Warranty claims must be made within the warranty period and require proof of service</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Liability and Disclaimers</h2>
        <h3>4.1 Limitation of Liability</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Our liability is limited to the cost of the service provided</li>
          <li>We are not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for loss of use, lost profits, or business interruption</li>
          <li>We are fully insured, but our insurance coverage does not extend to customer equipment beyond the scope of our service</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.2 Service Disclaimers</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>While we strive for accuracy, estimates are approximate and final costs may vary</li>
          <li>We cannot guarantee specific completion times due to unforeseen complications</li>
          <li>Emergency service response times are estimates and may vary based on location and current call volume</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for delays caused by weather, traffic, or other external factors</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.3 Equipment Damage</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>We exercise reasonable care in performing services, but we are not liable for damage to equipment that occurs during normal service operations</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for damage caused by pre-existing conditions, wear and tear, or equipment failure</li>
          <li>Customers are responsible for securing their equipment and removing personal items before service</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Customer Responsibilities</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide accurate information about equipment, location, and service needs</li>
          <li>Ensure equipment is accessible and safe for our technicians to work on</li>
          <li>Be present or available during service, or provide authorized representative</li>
          <li>Pay for services rendered in accordance with agreed-upon terms</li>
          <li>Follow any post-service instructions or recommendations provided</li>
          <li>Notify us immediately of any issues or concerns with completed work</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Cancellation and Refunds</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Cancellations made less than 2 hours before scheduled service may be subject to a cancellation fee</li>
          <li>No-shows may be charged a minimum service fee</li>
          <li>Refunds are provided at our discretion and only for services not performed</li>
          <li>Parts ordered specifically for your service are non-refundable once ordered</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All content on this website, including text, graphics, logos, and images, is the property of 
          NorthWestern Diesel and is protected by copyright and trademark laws. You may not reproduce, 
          distribute, or use our content without written permission.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Modifications to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be effective immediately 
          upon posting to our website. Continued use of our services after changes constitutes acceptance 
          of the modified terms.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of the state(s) in which we operate. Any disputes arising 
          from these terms or our services shall be resolved through appropriate legal channels.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these terms or to discuss service arrangements, please contact us:
        </p>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <p><strong>NorthWestern Diesel</strong></p>
          <p>Phone: <a href="tel:6825404507">(682) 540-4507</a></p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:donovanw@nwdieselco.com">donovanw@nwdieselco.com</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="acknowledgment">
          <p><strong>By requesting service from NorthWestern Diesel, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to these terms and disclaimers.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Page Hero */
  .page-hero {
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      rgba(210, 10, 15, 0.1) 0%,
      transparent 50%
    );
    background-color: var(--bg-dark);
  }

  .hero-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Legal Content Section */
  .legal-content-section {
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    background-color: var(--bg-dark);
  }

  .legal-content-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-content {
    background-color: var(--bg-card);
    padding: 3rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(210, 10, 15, 0.2);
  }

  .legal-intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .legal-content h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content ul ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .legal-content li strong {
    color: var(--text-light);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .legal-content a {
    color: var(--primary-blue);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .legal-content a:hover {
    color: var(--primary-red);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .contact-info {
    background-color: var(--bg-dark);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--primary-blue);
  }

  .contact-info p {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
    color: var(--text-light);
  }

  .contact-info strong {
    color: var(--white);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .acknowledgment {
    background-color: var(--bg-dark);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--primary-red);
  }

  .acknowledgment p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-light);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .acknowledgment strong {
    color: var(--primary-red);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page-hero,
    .legal-content-section {
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .legal-content {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .legal-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .legal-content h3 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
  }
</style>

